<dl id="n08070i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08070i">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08070i"> 70(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> express regret at not / having pronoun of / endearment</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">People who express regret at not having a pronoun of endearment &hellip; <font color="green">[such as <i>tu</i>]</font> &hellip; should consider that no foreign language has really a pronoun exclusively for the most intimate relations. <small> Otto Jespersen, <a name="OJGS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#OJGS"><cite title="source">The Growth and Structure of the English Language</cite></a>, 4th ed. (Jul 1923) 233</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
